name: Nel segno del dolore
Het Bobo beeldje
Il cammino della vita

description: Transported to a hospital for a sudden illness , for Dylan Dog begins an ordeal with no end in the worst of horrors : the disease . A dark evil has taken possession of him , torturing and consuming it day after day , without anyone being able to do anything to save it. The only way out seems to be to face the creature that is killing him , reaching her into the heart of suffering . A place that is just a step away from death .
name: Mater Morbi

description: Collecting the first five issues of the acclaimed new series from FABLES writer Bill Willingham! Join Nightmaster, Ragman, Nightshade, Blue Devil, Enchantress and Detective Chimp the mismatched magical heroes from DC's hit DAY OF VENGEANCE as they face brand-new villains!
name: The Pentacle Plot
Il giardino delle illusioni

description: As a teenager Eddie Patron had thought hed seen it all. That is until his nerdy friend Francis Keiser introduced him to the drug FLY. Now the skys the limit and Eddie is about to be introduced to a whole new world. A world that is not without its consequences. From the mind of the writer of Image Comics THE GIFT, Zenescopes WONDERLAND TRILOGY and THE WAKING comes Raven Gregorys latest tale of suspense set in a world where superheroes arent really heroes at all How far would you go to FLY? Featuring 4 covers by superstar artists Amanda Conner (Supergirl, The Pro), Darick Robertson (The Boys), Eric J (JSA, Rex Mundi), and Ale Garza (Fathom, Superman/Batman). As an added bonus retailers who order 20 copies of A, B, C, or D will receive a Darick Robertson sketch cover free. Dont miss the series that critics are raving about!

In the small town of Jericho, Texas, a yearly phenomenon known as the Jericho Lights brings tourists and UFO enthusiasts from miles around. Although the true cause of the strange dancing lights remains a mystery, they've become a deeply rooted part of Jericho's history. On the eve of this year's light show, something else returns to Jericho - 19 year old Zaya Vahn, who mysteriously vanished from the small town nearly 3 years ago. Heavily traumatized, it appears that Zaya has no memory of what happened to her. It soon becomes apparent that she may be keeping a few secrets which could blow open a sinister conspiracy stretching all the way back to the founding of Jericho.

The sins of Jericho are laid bare, the streets run with blood, and the hour of judgment is at hand. Don't miss the shocking conclusion to what The Fourth Rail calls "a sexy but quiet adventure into darkness."

With the link between Zaya, Jericho, and the Lights revealed, the judgment of the Harvesters appears imminent, leaving 4,000 souls hanging in the balance. Daniel may have the power to stop it - but will he?

As Daniel finally begins uncovering the truth about Zaya's abduction, he is faced with even bigger questions, like what is the 'Covenant Code' and who are the mysterious Harvesters? Meanwhile, the keepers of Jericho's 'dirty little secret' continue to turn up dead, forcing the remaining conspirators to take drastic measures in order to combat Zaya's wrath.

As the Jericho Lights continue to exhibit unusual behavior, the strange circumstances surrounding 19 year old Zaya Vahn only get stranger as Daniel begins connecting the dots, leading him to investigate not only the mayor, but the entire city council. Meanwhile, Sheriff Banks continues his search for the truth and discovers that even Daniel may have a few secrets of his own.

On the eve of the phenomenon known as the Jericho Lights, Zaya's return has not been the happy homecoming everyone expected. Dark secrets are being exposed and the dead bodies are piling up. Caught in the middle is internet reporter Daniel Webster, who may be onto the biggest story of his career...that is, if he can survive it.

The story of companions, Temperance and Amy, as they meet their destinies. Set in the "Texas Steampunk" world of 1897.

Introduction by Warren Ellis.
name: Clockwork Angels

description: Written by fan-favorite Howard Chaykin (Challengers of the Unknown, American Flagg), illustrated by comics legend Russ Heath (SGT. ROCK, "The Haunted Tank" ), and inspired by Philip Wylie's novel Gladiator, LEGEND is a 4-issue miniseries telling the story of Hugo Danner, a man blessed with super-human strength and invulnerability, but cursed with all-too-human failings. This miniseries details the physical, emotional and social ramifications of Hugo's abilities as he grows to manhood, desperately searching for acceptance and for the role he's meant to play in the world.
name: A Boy's Story

description: The engaging 4-issue drama by Howard Chaykin and Russ Heath continues! Hugo Danner's powers are both a blessing and a curse, a fact that becomes more apparent as he reaches his adolescent years! Invulnerability and incredible strength can't help him when it comes to dealing with love, heartache and human failings.
name: The Adventures of a Young Man

description: Torn by tragedy, Hugo questions his powers and wonders what his true purpose really is. As a way of atoning, he enlists in the Army to help his country during the Vietnam War. What will happen when he realizes that he cannot help resolve the conflict even with all his powers?
name: Rider of the Storm

description: The conclusion to Howard Chaykin's and Russ Heath's incredible story! Hugo Danner continues of search for his true self and his place in this world, but how can he help people when all they see is a pariah? And what happens when he realizes that all his powers cannot help him when his true foe is human nature?
name: A Man Among Men

description: The classic anime series is now an Antarctic Press full color comic series! The year is 1945. The Americans attack an uncharted Japanese island that holds a secret scientific base where scientists are working on a new kind of weapon-a giant robot known simply as The Ironman. Jump to the year 1961. A new criminal organization has threatened the governments of the world with an army of mechanical weapons and beasts. The freedom of the world rests on the collective shoulders a organization called the International Justice Organization. Meanwhile, in one of the IJO's secret labs, a new weapon for justice is being created, a weapon code-named: GIGANTOR. But the project is far from completion, and the lab has been infiltrated by a traitor!

A mysterious criminal organization calling itself the Red Reich has been using giant mechanical beasts to blackmail the world. The World Justice Organization, with the robot known as Gigantor in its ranks, is activated. However, the WJO's base is under attack, and Jimmy Sparks, the only person who can control Gigantor, is nowhere to be found!

A mysterious new robot is disrupting life in the Space Program, and its name is Black Ox. Can Gigantor defeat this new foe, or will he have finally met his match? Don't miss out on this hot new series with the Space-Age Robot!

Jimmy Sparks is puzzled to discover one day that Gigantor's movements aren't as effective as before. Dr. Brilliant examines the robot and finds out that it's a fake! Soon many Gigantors are sighted, leading to even more startling discoveries: Somebody is producing less effective replicas to hide the real one stolen right from Jimmy's complex. On top of that, the real Gigantor is under the control of Captain Spider and is now on its way to the Moon, where Spider is building a missile launch base so he can spray Earth with neutron bombs!

Captain Spider has stolen Gigantor and is using it to speed up the building of his Moon-base fortress. After realizing that his Gigantor is a inferior copy, Jimmy Sparks convinces Dick Strong and Inspector Blooper to assemble a task force to retrieve the real Gigantor from the Moon. But Spider discovers their plan through his network of spies and prepares a surprise party for them. Inspector Blooper's special Space Police force is about to face the Moon of Death!

Now that the Gigantor is back under Jimmy Sparks' control, he plans to have the space-age robot help Inspector Blooper's Space Police destroy Captain Spider's Moonbase of Death. But Spider has one more card up in his sleeve: When he had Gigantor under his control, he not only had it help build his moonbase, but also assist in constructing the mammoth Red Spider, a giant robot meant to succeed Gigantor by destroying it! Eight times as large and powerful as Gigantor, Red Spider will pit the Bigger-than-Big G against its greatest threat to survival!

A top-secret submarine is destroyed and the Iron Empire is blamed. However, after careful investigation by Inspector Blooper, agent Dick Strong and Jimmy Sparks, they begin to suspect that another enemy is at work, an enemy that has vowed vengence on all surface dwellers.

The undersea kingdoms of Mu and Atlantis have declared war on the surface world, and the Iron Empire is supplying the technology to control the seas! Gigantor is the world's only hope, but Jimmy Sparks and Inspector Blooper are prisoners! Will Bob Brilliant be able to control Gigantor enough to battle the undersea robots?

There is no end to the power of a brilliant mind, and few limits to the terror it can create when it is used for evil. Dr. Emeritus has created a small machine which can generate over 100,000 volts of electricity, but the invention has caused him attention both welcome and unwelcome! Armed with this device, criminals could use it for their own ends and create havoc. Can Reeny, Dr.Emeritus' daughter, safely transport this potential weapon to Bob Brilliant?

Dr. Emeritus has created a small machine which can generate over 100,000 volts of electricity, but the invention has caused him attention both welcome and unwelcome! Reeny and Jimmy Sparks are kidnapped by a evil scientist intent upon using the device to power his own giant robot so he can use it to destroy Gigantor and conquer the world!

Mysterious UFOs are plaguing the skies and no one can stop them, not even Gigantor. Armed with a new ray weapon, the ships are able to knock even the mighty Gigantor from the sky! When Dr. Bob Brilliant attempts to create a countermeasure to this ray, he is kidnapped by a criminal organization run by the madman Ugablob!

Ugablob's scheme to brainwash Dr. Brilliant is underway. Gigantor and company race against the clock to save him. Can they stop Ugablob once and for all, or are they already too late? This is the FINAL ISSUE of the Gigantor maxiseries, so be sure you catch it!
In a dramatic culmination, Paul hunts down his nemesis, Luke, forcing a violent confrontation in a last ditch effort to save his family. But a terrible revelation awaits...

description: The Rebel, Part One. Douglas Pistoia is a new kind of soldier, his missions broadcast live on television for rating and profit, and he's becoming a media star. After a few days relaxing in Mexico City, Doug and his unit return to the field, arriving at a deserted village on the border between Argentina and Chile - deserted, because its inhabitants have been methodically massacred...
name: The Rebel
